🐝🐝🐝 We’re on the set of “Yellowjackets” with Canadian actress @sophie__nelisse (Sophie Nélisse). 
 
“I forget that the clothes were clean at the beginning; I don’t even notice the transition myself. Guess you’ll have to keep watching to see why we get so dirty.” 
 
To celebrate the show’s new season on @showtime, step into a thrilling (and slightly messy) world as Sophie takes us behind the scenes on a typical shoot day in Vancouver. From shocking wardrobe changes to on set snacks with her costars-turned-besties, anticipate blood, dirt and… yogurt?!

My last two brain cells🥴
Festivities🥂
Right before our anchor got stuck under a chain and we had no other option than to cut it off. The boat rental dude is not too happy with us.
Currently stranded in Hvar because we got on the wrong ferry. Before you ask, no, there are no more ferries left for the day. So here’s my dump as it seems we’ll be stuck on this island forever.

If you must know, this has been the best trip of my entire life. Even the 6h bus ride at 2am with no aircon, the sketchiest toilet I’ve ever had to use and the remarquably loud snoring man to my left.
Am I in denial of being back home? Yes, yes I am.

Irena’s Vow will be premiering at TIFF this coming Sunday.

I feel so incredibly touched to have been able to bring Irena’s story to life. A tribute to her courage and strength, to the many lives she has saved.

I also have so much appreciation for this Canadian / Polish coproduction. We’ve fought endless battles to make this project come true. The dedication of every single cast and crew member is truly what made this movie so special. 

@loulouarchambault je t’aime plus plus plus plus plus, à l’infini des plus.
